# Master Specification: Project Digital Plaid (2026 Edition)

## I. Technical Architecture & Stack
- **Frontend**: React Native (Expo) with NativeWind (Tailwind CSS).
- **Backend**: Supabase (Auth, PostgreSQL, Real-time Listeners, Edge Functions).
- **Offline-First Resilience**: Mandatory local caching via SQLite/AsyncStorage. "Check-ins" and "Sentiment Data" must persist during signal dead zones and sync upon reconnection.
- **Battery Strategy**:
    - **Strict No-GPS Rule**: Location is inferred from the "Last Completed Step."
    - **Lazy Fetching**: Data pings only on Step Completion, Manual Recalibration, or Mobile Order triggers. No background polling.
- **Platform**: PWA for initial MVP, moving to Native for Live Activity (Lock Screen) support.

## II. Core Feature Set
### 1. Unified Group Intake & Profile Management
- **Demographic Detail**: Tracks Name, Age, Gender, and Height (Hard requirement for Rider Switch).
- **Link-Share Survey**: Unique URL for guests. Leader can complete for others (toddlers/seniors).
- **Multi-Dimensional Preferences**:
    - **Rides**: Must-Do, Like-to-Do, Will Avoid.
    - **Characters**: Must-Meet (Furry vs. Face), Like-to-Meet, Avoid.
    - **Foodie Profile**: Allergies (auto-filtering), Cuisine (Adventurous/Safe), Style (Quick/Dining).
- **Ambition Metric**: "The Completionist" vs. "The Relaxed Parent."
- **Stamina Check**: "Walking Capacity" score (1–10) to cluster activities geographically.

### 2. 2026 Temporal Rule Engine
- **Regional Awareness**:
    - **Disneyland (DL/DCA)**: Day-of LL booking; 5-min walking buffers; DCA 25th Anniversary overlays.
    - **Disney World (WDW)**: Pre-booking (7/3 days); LL Multi Pass Tiers (1x Tier-1, 2x Tier-2); 45-min transportation buffers.
- **2026 Hard-Coded Refurbishments**:
    - **WDW**: Big Thunder Mountain (Spring overhaul), Buzz Lightyear, Rock 'n' Roller Coaster (retiring March 2).
    - **DL**: Jungle Cruise (Feb), Space Mountain (Late Feb).
- **Special Events**: Support for "Hard-Ticket" events and EPCOT Festivals (Booth Crawl logic).

### 3. Tactical Coach & "Family Peace" Logic
- **Rider Switch "Double-Block"**:
    - 1.5x duration multiplier for height-restricted rides.
    - Generates a "Waiting Parent Sub-Step" with nearby low-wait/sensory-friendly activity suggestions.
- **The "Task Killer"**: Character Dining reservations automatically mark characters as "Met."
- **Mobile Order Watchdog**:
    - "Hanger Prevention": Suggests "Snack Clusters" based on location.
    - Lead-Time Alerts: [Target] - [Lead] - 10m buffer.
- **Recalibration (Tolerance Threshold)**: Only prompts a pivot if a "Must-Do" wait increases by >20 mins or attraction closes.
- **The Persona**: "Tactical Expert" coach (Narrative, expert context, coaching-style).

### 4. Mini Memory Maker (The Recap)
- **Digital Scrapbook**: Automated end-of-day JSON and UI view.
- **Planned vs. Actual**: Vertical side-by-side timeline.
- **The Trophy Case**: "Wait Time Defeated," "Characters High-Fived," "Hidden Mickeys Found."
- **Sentiment Mapping**: Joy Graph mapping emojis against the timeline.
- **Nudge Log**: Captures completed "Contextual Nudges" (Photo-ops, Sensory, Trivia).

## III. UX/UI Design Philosophy
- **Theme**: "Executive Plaid" (Forest Green #1B3022, Cream #F4F1DE, Gold #D4AF37).
- **Accessibility**: "Sunlight Mode" (Ultra-high contrast). Primary text 16pt+ sans-serif.
- **One-Handed Navigation**: Interactive elements in the bottom 30% of the screen.
- **Touch Targets**: Minimum 48x48 pixels.
- **Recalibrate Button**: Accessible but requires a **2-second hold** to prevent pocket triggers.
- **Presence Nudges**: Itinerary-triggered alerts (e.g., Tangled lanterns).

## IV. Logic Edge Cases & Compliance
- **Multi-Park Trips**: Logic set flips per day based on ParkID.
- **Character Interaction**: Alerts 15m before scheduled appearance nearby.
- **Liability**: "Advisor" status only; user performs manual booking to avoid "Bot" bans.

## V. Hand-off Summary
1. **Initialize**: Supabase schema (Trips, Guests, Surveys, ItineraryHistory).
2. **Constraint Logic**: Prioritize HeightConflict checks before any ride suggestion.
3. **Optimization**: Implement "Character-to-Dining" overlap.
4. **UI**: High-contrast, bottom-heavy, 2-second recalibrate hold.
